<br>
<br>
Through a series of events today on the test server i believe i have undeniable proof as to the bugginess of phys init with fists. More specifically, i should say that phys init is not bugged, it does not work period. In fact i have discovered that fist speed is solely based on MELEE INIT rather than phys as it should be. This is how i came upon this revelation : <br>
<br>
I had found a ql 142 extreme low-light scope that i intended to equip for the +11 crit chance. Once i recieved the maestro buffs to fit on the scope, i proceeded to test my crit rate. After a few tries, i began to notice that i was hitting slower with my fists now, eventhough my aggro bar was at full aggresive. This certainly couldn't have been the case, since i had 924 phys init before i equipped the scope which deducts 565 from phys, melee, and ranged init, leaving me with 359 phys init still remaining. Sure enough though, i was punching at about the rate i usually see from setting my aggro bar to 1/2. This made me think back to the guesses among the MA community about fist speed being based on melee init rather than phys. It would certainly make sense in this scenario, with my melee init now at around -300 (i didnt record the actual number). So being in the unique position of having tons of extra IP still at lvl 190 i decided to max my melee init skill, which put it at 726 total, or 161 with the scope equipped. Sure enough, when i tested now with the scope penalty i was punching at full speed once again at full aggressive. I then took off the scope and thought to myself &quot;if the 600 init = -1/-2 sec theory of init usage is true, then with 726 melee init i should be able to set my aggro bar to 1/2 and see no slow down of fists, which i always expected with 600+ phys init but never saw.&quot; And what happened? With 1/2 aggressive i saw no difference between the speed of that setting and full aggressive.<br>
<br>
All of these facts together surely must convince FC that the init assigned to govern fist speed is erroneous. To me it seems fairly easy to fix - simply switch the melee to phys. This should make right in practice was was intended in design. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=keldrys>Keldrys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Peking Duck</span><br>  Posts: 105<br> <font color=#660000>(3/25/02 8:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1825.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> All of these problems seem to be centered around the use of a LLS.  With this new information it seems to me that it's not phys init that's broken but rather LLS's.  Maybe it's a bug where it switches you from phys init to melee init when you equip a LLS.  Excellent work on this issue, hopefully the bug team will figure it out and I can put my LLS back on. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=chronita>Chronita</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#660000>(3/25/02 12:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1825.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> Yes i considered that it was perhaps the scope screwing with the init, but i believe its an overall bug. My reasoning behind this is that i can now set my aggro bar to 1/2 with no scope on and 726 melee init and see no slow down in fists. Before when i just had 