<br>
Now the only surefire way I've found to fix this is to hit the mob with a special attack or any aggro prod (it does 1 nano dmg).  This 'resets' the mob's hp to the correct lvl and you can continue.  You have to do it after you've delivered your phantom damage.  Other than that you have to hope a mob heals itself which will also correct the sync problem. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=suber>suber</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.anarchy-online.com/character/photos/40258.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#660000>(3/27/02 2:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1825.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.anarchy-online.com/character/photos/40258.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: @#$%</span><hr size=1> Hm, I am still sceptical, I must admit <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
